{"word":"ἀσεβέω","slug":"ἀσεβέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀσεβέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:ἀσεβής'><el>ἀσεβής</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to be impious, to act profanely, sin against the gods</i>; <el>εἴς τινα</el> or <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>περί τινα</el> or <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to sin against</i> him, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; hence in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ἠσέβηται οὐδέν</el> no <i>sin has been committed</i>, <b><a href='S:Andocides'>Andoc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}